"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"we were welcomed like we were part of the Greek family. they were warm and accommodating even though we were 30 minutes late from our reservation timing. <br><br>we were whisked up to the third floor that brought abt memories of my time in the Greek islands - except that the view is of Bukit Timah Road and not the ocean and the sunset. but the interior of the restaurant is truly 100% greek - with olive oil tins lining the stairwell and memorabilia from Greece. its more than just a restaurant but an experience.<br><br>the food - is all Greek to me! everything is so well made you just get lost in the quality and quantity of the food. you can taste the passion and love in their cooking! I dont need to buy a plane ticket to Athens anymore! i can just take a bus or cab if i am feeling rich to reminisce my love of all things Greek.<br><br>And the dessert course - i have to admit greek desserts are VERY VERY sweet but it is memorable with the way they are served. loved the touch that they do special dessert for special days like valentines.<br><br>Service - impeccable.  server&#39;s attention to detail and attentiveness to all the queries is impressive. patience is also top notch. i was probably asking the dumbest questions but he never once got mad. he even brought me a rose cos its valentines! #aww! he even gave recommendations and advised us from over ordering and he was right! also told us about the special dessert for the night. the owners also came by to check on us and asked for our opinions.<br><br>truly an experience worthy of michelin stars right here in the heart of Singapore.",
