"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"Oh mah gosh. This chicken is magic. This batter, this juicy flesh, is tasty, tasty magic. I cannot be more thankful for the person who brought this here to our shores.<br><br>You walk into this dingy mall, and it&#39;s a little bit like ascending to the heavens - hop on the escalator, and... escalate to chicken-y delights. I kid you not, it&#39;s right there at the top of the escalator, on the second floor.<br><br>Eating here? Order from the first guys you see. Then grab a seat. But if you&#39;re taking it away, then head straight to the main counter, and tackle that massive menu sitting before you. I got a little lost today - I&#39;ve been fortunate to have people buy this to parties so I&#39;ve never had to buy this myself before this experience, but I knew what my end goal was, so I did not allow myself to be fazed. After all, I had this chicken in my sights.<br><br>First-timers? You&#39;ll want a two-piece meal. Hungry? Try the half-spring meal. Me? I&#39;ll have both please. Once you see that chicken, you might forget that the coleslaw serving is tiny. Thank goodness the fries are decent, but mostly, that chicken will turn any frown upside down.",
