"reviewcomment":"Great new-comer to the restaurant scene. Picked this for a special date and couldn&#39;t be more satisfied with my choice. First things first, this restaurant is a little out of the way so be prepared to take a cab or have a ride. Located right at the heart of Labrador Park, it isn&#39;t anywhere near the main road. But that&#39;s exactly what I love about it. When the cab driver dropped us off, all we could see was a flickering trail of tea light candles marking the way.<br><br>The restaurant sits amidst lush greenery and gives you the wonderful feeling of escaping the humdrum of the city. The dining area is perched out into the trees and well-ventilated by ceiling fans. I seem to be rambling on just bout the decor but you have to see it to know why I am raving about it.<br><br>Food-wise, I am very finicky when it comes to fusion but Eco does it perfectly, marrying various flavours without a glitch. Had the Tuna Tataki for starters and the seared fish paired well with the hints of ginger and orange. This was followed by the sea bass and the freshness of the dish easily made it stand out. Partner had the squid risotto and couldn&#39;t stop raving about it, so that will be a good bet too.<br><br>Great place for a long dinner with someone you don&#39;t mind having a 3 hour conversation with.",
