"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"This was an excelllent dining experience.<br><br>We decided to meet at Chijmes and then select a place to eat.  I had been told Japanese Dining Sun was very good.  However, when we checked, they said it would be at least an hour before we could be seated.<br><br>Earlier, we had noticed Tatsu and that it was not very busy.  We circled back and were quickly seated at their dining bar.<br><br>The ambiance is sparse but stylish.  The service is impeccable with definite touches o Japanese conservatism.<br><br>Very soon, we were enjoying a very nice sake and placing our order.<br><br>The food arrived in a steady stream.<br><br>First up, was the sushi plate and the fried fish.<br><br>My friend does not eat raw fish.   So, I tackled most of the nigiri and she went to work on the rolls.  It was all delicious.  The fish was very fresh and of the highest quality.  The flavors were so delicate.  The vinegar rice was also well prepared.<br><br><a href='/redir?url=http%3A%2F%2Ftinyurl.com%2F8obdqmt&amp;s=66498b0ede764b3bac454d87d0372ff9e2e91c79972f0a5de62491eefd928ea8' target='_blank' rel='nofollow'>tinyurl.com/8obdqmt</a><br><br>Along with the sushi, they brought the fried fish dish.  This was the least impressive part of the meal.  There wasn&#39;t anything particulary wrong with it.  The dish simply did not stand out.<br><br><a href='/redir?url=http%3A%2F%2Ftinyurl.com%2Fd9fkpyz&amp;s=47b0bd048d0b117993baf69248e821065c9a9882ac93b66aff69c294def1d650' target='_blank' rel='nofollow'>tinyurl.com/d9fkpyz</a><br><br>The next dish to arrive was the clams in broth.  This was a very light dish with very subtle flavors.  My friend was in heaven.<br><br><a href='/redir?url=http%3A%2F%2Ftinyurl.com%2F8na8qfb&amp;s=7ce538596287c72682f6f6183fda9d6a1169aca220902b9fad306f12b7a90dd0' target='_blank' rel='nofollow'>tinyurl.com/8na8qfb</a><br><br>Also, at this time, they brought out the baked clam dish.  In comparison to the mild clams in broth, this was very rich with cheese and strong savoury flavors.<br><br><a href='/redir?url=http%3A%2F%2Ftinyurl.com%2F932msx5&amp;s=914159c8c1f81c5fca6b3fef0f8fb55385d41029df9c23126b143e545da60632' target='_blank' rel='nofollow'>tinyurl.com/932msx5</a><br><br>The last dish was the pork belly.  Along with the sushi, for me, this was the highlight of the meal.<br><br><a href='/redir?url=http%3A%2F%2Ftinyurl.com%2F8vssstd&amp;s=6ab60a39b64aaf4dde66ae24bf0d971ff0378fc6b66931a05ad4dd84be867142' target='_blank' rel='nofollow'>tinyurl.com/8vssstd</a><br><br>I am not sure why this restaurant isn&#39;t always packed.  It is a wonderful culinary delight.  The ambiance, food, and service provide a seamless enjoybale experience.",
