"reviewcomment":"I would move to Singapore for JiBiru.  Well, I would move there anyway, but I digress.  What a fantastic concept to specialize in the growing craft beer offerings from Japan.  The presence of a place like this speaks volumes to the growing craft beer culture emerging in Singapore, which has improved dramatically in the 2 years since my last visit.<br><br>Prior to my visit to JiBiru, my knowledge of Japanese craft beer was limited to Hitachino.  While they do have a lengthy list of options from that brewery (both on tap and in bottles), they also have pages and pages from 7-8 other Japanese producers.  In addition just to round things out, they carry a few European and Australian beers as well.  My colleague and I were only able to sample a fraction of what was offered, requiring a few returns to try out the rest of the list.<br><br>Although we only got a couple of small plates (pan fried gyoza and chicken wings), the food was quite delicious and pairs well with the beer.<br><br>Service was just OK.  More often than not, we had to flag down our waiter to order more beer, even though the place was less than half full.<br><br>People watching is quite excellent, as JiBiru is situated near one of the entrances to the 313@Somerset mall.",
