"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"If you love your sake, this is the place in Singapore!  This is a traditional Japanese sake bar and you should expect to be surrounded by bibulous company, no less.<br><br>Sato-san, the boss is also a supplier of sake to many other establishments in Singapore.  The range of sake over here is astonishing, more than even the liquor shop at Daimaru.  You can have the cheapest to the most expensive bottle here.  I know cos&#39; I had to foot the bill for last Friday&#39;s drink - almost $500 (incl taxes) for a large bottle of  Dassai 23 Junmai Daiginjyo and 2 portions of oden (what I would call Japanese Yong Tau Foo) for pre-dinner drinks for 3.  You can also order some selected yakitori which is served from the adjacent Tori Tama restaurant.  But, go with the oden, at least that&#39;s what I assuage myself with cos&#39; it&#39;s healthy and guilt-free.<br><br>The deco is spartan by most standards in Singapore, one L shaped counter with 4 counter chairs (used to be 2) and the rest would have to stand.  Not too bad cos&#39; if you can&#39;t stand anymore, it means it&#39;s time to call it a night!  Actually, there&#39;s a little small round table right at the back, with 3 crates which have been strapped with cushions to act as chairs.  There&#39;s also the outdoor seating which can take 10 or so.  <br><br>They also serve a good range of Japanese whiskey and beers, if that&#39;s your poison.  There&#39;s also a great selection of umeshu, if that is your preference too.  We come for the sake ..... don&#39;t worry if you can&#39;t finish your bottle, they will keep it for you for your next visit.",
