"ogimage":"http://s3-media3.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/ApaKvaqRPAZ_hmfLL1r6bg/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"People who know me would know that I don&#39;t give five stars very easily. I only ordered a few dishes but they were all very good. And I was blown away by the salmon belly sashimi. It is just so hard to find good salmon belly sashimi, and it is ironic that I find the best salmon belly sashimi not in california, not in japan (at least where I&#39;ve been) but here in Singapore. In general, my attitude towards japanese food in Singapore is &#34;jaded&#34;. I feel like in order to get decent sashimi, you usually have to pay an arm and a leg. And usually when I do, I am not impressed by the quality. This salmon belly is well marbled with fat, super fresh, and evey slightly sweet! Even at 6 bucks a slice, I am willing to pay it. The chef recommendation&#39;s seasonal dish, salmon roe with soy sauce and yuzu was another winner. The salmon roe was not at all salty (which means it&#39;s fresh) and lightly seasoned with soy sauce, and the yuzu just brings finesse to it. The grilled saba was decent, but not impressive. Will definitely come back for the omakase or chirashi or just a sushi meal. Thank you for making me believe in Singapore again!",
