"rating":"5.0",
"reviewcomment":"I had pulled an all nighter and went here for a set lunch to give myself an incentive to stay awake until an afternoon meeting. I had the tomato with lentils and duck pieces, the lamb with pureed potatoes, and the poached pear with chocolate ganache dessert.<br><br>The tomato filling was very carefullly seasoned and flavorful, and paired well with a fresh arugula salad. The lamb was a reasonably sized portion. I had asked for medium but the server said it was served medium rare, and, while not what I ordered, I think in retrospect that was probably a good thing because it was juicy and soft. It looked so good I forgot to take a picture before eating it. The dessert had slices of pear, little crispy piece of chocolate granola, a scoop of very good vanilla ice cream, a few berries, and three blocks of dark chocolate dusted with cocoa powder.<br><br>Overall, a great meal. Not cheap, but reasonable for the quality. The flavors all came together and they clearly paid attention to the details.",
