"ogimage":"http://s3-media1.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/rT_eYTdxqlAX_nRzglQFUw/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"I&#39;m happy that there&#39;s Soup Spoon, I honestly am.  Has it really been 10 years??!   That&#39;s been quite a bit of time to keep coming back only for ONE thing.    Ok, so I&#39;m weird that way, but I have a hard time admitting that I really dig fungi...not to cultivate (although I&#39;ve tried my hand at it; it is a good time), but to eat.   I enjoy earthy flavors and few of nature&#39;s wonders are as adept as the mushroom in representing this flavor without the cloying bitter hints (not to mention the grit) of actual dirt.  If it isn&#39;t already clear to you by now, I visit Soup Spoon only to get at their Velvety Mushroom Stroganoff.   I like this product so much that I didn&#39;t take issue with them calling this entirely vegetarian offering a stroganoff. <br><br>I usually get the take home packs.   I do this because as the soup is gently reheating in a saucepan, I stir in Tamari (Kikkoman).  The earthiness of the shiitakes is coaxed out a little more by the wheaty hints of the Tamari.  Of course, the fact that there&#39;s alcohol in the Tamari helps.   A totally legal way of getting a head trip with mushrooms.",
