"ogimage":"http://s3-media1.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/Clrqf5UjXZQpnOrwGp0ArQ/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"If you want a burger, and I mean, a great burger, go to a place that serves nothing else. <br><br>My brother in law and I have been on the great beef hunt over the last year or so, this naturally includes great steaks and great burgers! In my opinion De Burg is way up there on the &#39;great burger&#39; chart.<br><br>The place is open air and self service. You grab a menu and order, come back to collect your burger when it is ready. I waited 10 minutes. The kitchen is also open and while ordering I watched as the cooks crafted each burger individually with TLC. <br><br>The menu is very extensive and with only burgers in mind. Beef, pork, seafood, lamb, chicken and vegan are all available. 50 to 200 grams and Wagyu on the 200g if you wanted premium. Price points were $5 to $30. Then they had signature burgers. The person next to me had a monster of a burger and I inquired which one it was. He said he ordered the &#39;Desiree&#39;  I looked at the menu and it was described as chips, bacon and cheese hidden between 200g Aussie strip loin and 200g Aussie Lamb!! I was amazed he finished it. Other burgers had portobello mushrooms, iberico chorizo, and even a deep fried Spam ring.<br><br>Lost with so much choice I meekly chose the bacon cheese burger with a side of fries and tatted tots. That first bite is heavenly. Crispy bacon. Lovely medium rare Australian strip loin patty, hint of BBQ sauce and greens. All stacked within 2 soft and fluffy buns. In my view this is near perfection. I will be back to try the other burgers but I can see this be a regular place to satisfy my burger cravings.",
