"ogimage":"http://s3-media3.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/TELqYahZ6EpnUxLwfyUagw/l.jpg",
"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"This place is just so darn cute!<br>The kitchen staff wear I heart pho t-shirts with the singapore flag in the heart, they have signs showing how to get a table &amp; order (pretty straight forward but it was quiet when I went, judging by previous reviews this isn&#39;t normally the case), and they even have little ceramic-y prison style cups to keep the ordering sheets and pencils in, even if the food was only so-so I&#39;d go back just for the look of the place! <br><br>I was very excited to be back on yelp soil, but not so much I couldn&#39;t stay away from more Bahn Mi! To be honest, I didn&#39;t expect a lot after spending the last couple of weeks in Vietnam, but boy was I wrong! <br><br>I has the cold meat &amp; pâté Bahn Mi without chilli (of course), and it was delicious! Ok, so not quite &#34;man up the end of the street from my hostel&#34; delicious, but as good as I&#39;ve had outside of Vietnam! There was a slight kick to the flavoured mayo, but anyone with normal taste buds wouldn&#39;t have even noticed. <br><br>I like the dim sum style fill in a form ordering, and you have to get your own utensils &amp; napkins, but they still bring your dish to you. <br><br>I also had a (small) bottle of water, and came to $7.50, which for what I&#39;ve experienced in Singapore (outside of Chinatown) is pretty good <br><br>You should check it out!",
