"reviewcomment":"I didn&#39;t even know I liked German food until Magma.<br><br>The best part about Magma is the wine shop: Wines you can&#39;t find anywhere else in Singapore, all from Germany and all reasonably priced by Singapore standards. We usually buy wines as gifts here for friends and the feedback has been great. Recommend the Juliussital Riesling, which is not too sweet and comes in a unique bottle.<br><br>Also amazing: Their wine menu, which is basically a chart. So many times I never know what bottle to order, but Magma lists out for you by taste/type/region/flavor, making the whole experience a little less daunting. <br><br>Food: my favorite dish is the &#34;Rheinischer Sauerbraten,&#34; 7 days pickled braised beef in red wine gravy, potato dumpling, red cabbage &amp; raisins. I usually am not a beef eater, but this beef is so tender, soft and delicious. <br><br>They also host tasting events featuring various German wine experts which are usually a great way to learn more about the region and it&#39;s wine, plus sample the food if the idea of German food is new to you.<br><br>Lastly, they allow my dog to sit with me on the outside porch, and never fail to give the little guy some water, all with a smile. Little things go a long way.",
