"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"There always seem to be a long queue and usually when that happens you can&#39;t get seated until everyone&#39;s arrived, but it&#39;s so so worth it!<br><br>There are four staples that I ALWAYS get when here. Start with the cockles - even if the thought of having them raw irked me a ilttle but I love this enough to get myself a hepatitis B jab so I feel safe chomping down on these babies. What really makes it so good is the sauce with lots of garlic, so make sure you drown your cockle in it before throwing it down the deep end!<br><br>My favourite is their three egg spinach, with salted, centuy and the normal egg, a dish I began to notice was in restaurants everywhere, but only after I had it here. To date I still find this the most well done, with such a yum  gravy you&#39;d want to get rice with it. <br><br>The butter pork is an absolute winner. It seems to be fried pork ribs (boneless) buried under a mountain of milk powder, yet the powder is so sweet my friend guessed that it would perhaps be condensed milk powder, if such a thing even exists? But the novelty and goodness of the powder aside, the pork ribs are fried perfectly - not too thick, not fatty, very crispy...it is best eaten hot of course.<br><br>I also always get the golden mushroom beancurd, even if it has disappointed me on a few occassions. It&#39;s essentially those japanese straw mushrooms in a thick minced pork sauce, a little sweet but very full of flavour.<br><br>I have genuinely never thought I&#39;d need to try anything else.",
