"reviewcomment":"What a cool place for a coffee break or lunch! I had the veggie sandwich and it was incredibly tasty! It had tomato, arugula, cheddar cheese, and caramalized onions in balsamic vinegar! The best part of it was the sun dried tomato bread! All the flavors work so well together! <br><br>My friends and I ordered the same coffee beans (Columbian) prepared three different ways (all I can remember right now is the siphon...it looked like a science experiment). The barista, Nora, was so patient and friendly, and came to our table to explain the different steps and temperature etc. I didn&#39;t know making a cup of coffee can be this complicated! The three different methods produced such different flavors from the same beans!! That was so incredible! They also provided us with wine glasses to drink the coffee in! It was a coffee tasting experience! You&#39;d think something like this would cost a lot but it was so reasonably priced! It&#39;s cheaper than getting a latte at Starbucks and so much tastier! Plus you&#39;re supporting a local cafe in a great location. <br><br>Highly recommended!!",
