"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"I came here by myself after work and sat at the bar counter (kinda awkward sitting in a table when all the other tables are pairs...). I like sitting on the counter though, you get to peek at one the cooks are doing through a glass pane.<br><br>Like everyone said, the decor of this place is super cute and cozy, modeled after a small B&amp;B or something. They also play this adorable jazzy french music in the background.<br><br>I got the sizzling hamburg steak since that seems to be getting rave reviews. It&#39;s not bad for $19.90. Tasty and fills me up - it comes with fries and a bed of bean sprouts. Kinda reminds me of a glorified pepper lunch. It was served in an interesting manner too - The waiter will pour some sort of liquid on your egg and burger, and it would light up for awhile before she pours another liquid on top of it to put the fire out.<br><br>After serving your meal, your waiter will give you a key which you will then take to the cashier to pay your bill and &#34;check out&#34; of this lovely B&amp;B. cute eh?",
