"reviewcomment":"Good dimsum and insanely crowded on a weekend - even with reservations you still have to wait for awhile, and their front entrance is clogged with people.<br><br>Still when you do finally make it in, service is pretty prompt, and you can order off the various carts that get wheeled around, or off the menu. Bonus points if you can do it in Cantonese of course, but the service staff can do English decently and are quite friendly. Also, do drink the &#39;Gong Fu Cha&#39; in the tiny little teacups at the start and end of the meal - it&#39;s quite strong but supposed to be good as an appetiser and for digestion.<br><br>What&#39;s good: Deep fried fish skin, Custard buns (liu sha bao), the mixed plate had great BBQ pork (shao rou), duck and char siew. The congee was also very good - silky texture and tasty without being too much - you could walk over to the live station and order the more common congees, but the special flavoured ones had to be ordered.",
